==Production==
Karthik Krish,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tamilimdb.com/film/kappal/|title=Kappal|work=tamilimdb.com}}</ref> who had apprenticed under director [[S. Shankar|Shankar]] in ''[[Enthiran]]'' (2010), wrote the comedy script and had hoped to sign either actors [[Jai (actor)|Jai]] or [[Sivakarthikeyan]] for the role, before selecting [[Vaibhav Reddy|Vaibhav]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlykollywood.com/how-vaibhav-replaced-sivakarthikeyan-kappal/|title=How Vaibhav replaced Sivakarthikeyan|author=Surendhar MK|work=Only Kollywood}}</ref> The film began its shoot in March 2013 with scenes shot in Chennai with the lead cast. Initially [[Ashrita Shetty]] had signed up to portray the film's lead actress but delays meant that she was replaced by newcomer [[Sonam Bajwa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news-interviews/Vaibhavs-Kappal-sails-in-the-night/articleshow/19274893.cms|title=Vaibhav's Kappal sails in the night!|work=The Times of India}}</ref> [[Natarajan Sankaran]] replaced [[Santhosh Narayanan]] as the film's music composer,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kollyinsider.com/2014/04/shankars-assistant-brings-us-colorful.html|title=Shankar’s assistant brings us colorful 'Kappal'|work=Tamil Cinema News&nbsp;— Movie Reviews&nbsp;— Gossips}}</ref> although the latter agreed to sing a song for the film's soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://silverscreen.in/news/santhosh-narayanan-sings-for-kappal/|title=Santhosh Narayanan Sings For Kappal|work=Silverscreen.in}}</ref>

In April 2014, the film began another schedule with the director remarking that Vaibhav's character in the film would have shades of the role portrayed by [[Karthik (actor)|Karthik]] in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s ''[[Mouna Ragam]]'' (1986).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-vaibhav-reddy-has-mouna-ragam-karthik-attitude-in-kappal-director-1982604|title=Vaibhav Reddy has 'Mouna Ragam' Karthik attitude in 'Kappal': Director|work=dna}}</ref> After a successful screening in September 2014, director [[S. Shankar|Shankar]] bought the film and made plans to release it, marking a comeback to film production after a four-year hiatus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/kappal-goes-to-shankar/article6394429.ece?secpage=true&secname=entertainment|title=Kappal goes to Shankar|author=Srinivasa Ramanujam|work=The Hindu}}</ref>

==Soundtrack==
The music and background score of the film were composed by [[Natarajan Sankaran]]. The soundtrack features six tracks that belonged to varied genres,{{citation needed|date=April 2017}} one of them being a remix of the song "Ooru Vittu Ooru Vandhu", originally composed by [[Ilaiyaraaja]] for ''[[Karagattakaran]]'' (1989).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/blames-the-director-for-remixing-his-composition-without-permission/article6749679.ece|title=Ilayaraja sends legal notice on copyright to director Shankar|work=The Hindu|accessdate=18 April 2017}}</ref> The soundtrack album was released on 22 November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/Kappal-audio-launched/articleshow/45248623.cms|title=Kappal audio launched|work=The Times of India}}</ref>  ''Kappal'''s songs topped in FM station like the [[Radio Mirchi]] Top 5 for six weeks and the Suryan FM Top 10 and held 2nd place in the iTunes chart for two weeks, especially ''Kadhal Cassatta'', which became the most favourite song in all stations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.suryanfm.in/chennai/Chart/index.aspx|title=Welcome to Suryan FM|work=suryanfm.in}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiomirchi.com/more/tamil-top-20/ |title=Latest Tamil Songs: Top 20 Tamil Songs, Listen Best Tamil Songs Online&nbsp;— Radio Mirchi |work=radiomirchi.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213144942/http://www.radiomirchi.com/more/tamil-top-20/ |archivedate=13 December 2014 |df= }}</ref>

